"I remember the first read-thru. Hearing the play aloud for, in essence, the first time. The memories of much of my life flooded in. It reminded me of all of the many concessions I, as a Black man, was expected to make, had to make, while dealing in a white-run world. The racial bias, the jokes, the being the “1” in the room, the “1” in the cast. I can only speak for working in this business. While I was working my way up in the theater, I was most likely the only “1”. If not the “1”, I was 1/2 of the Black couple. Off to the side or in the back—or once in a while featured for a moment in the front because I was Black. The Boys in the Band reiterated all of those memories for me partially because of when it was written and the time frame it represented." - Kevyn Morrow Our first WWH of 2022 just dropped and it's written by Kevyn Morrow! Kevyn takes us back 12 years to when he was asked to join our 2010 production of The Boys in the Band. Thank you for sharing this, Kevin. Read The “1” and Only // By Kevyn Morrow http://transportgroup.org/project/the-1-and-only/

We offer HIV, STI and Hepatitis C testing and treatment, including Rapid HIV testing with results available in 20 minutes and Rapid ART* treatment in 1 – 3 days. Our STI panel includes Syphilis, Gonorrhea and Chlamydia. Call (949) 809-8764 for an appointment today. While progress has been made and new HIV diagnoses among Black Americans fell 7% between 2014 to 2018, Black Americans still accounted for nearly half (42%) of all new HIV diagnoses in 2018 and the highest rate of new diagnoses than any other racial or ethnic group. Social and structural inequities experienced by the Black community may leave individuals at increased risk for HIV and make them less likely to receive the care they need. The recent COVID-19 pandemic has also disproportionately impacted communities of color, exacerbating the health disparities and inequities that continue to affect the Black community. *Rapid ART refers to starting HIV treatment as soon as possible after the diagnosis of HIV infection. It is the action of starting treatment on the first visit of the new diagnosis preferably on the same day of diagnosis.

Low Carb Slow Cooker Five Spice Chicken Chinese Five Spice Powder is a spice blend available in either the spice section, or the Asian or ethnic food section, of most major supermarkets. My bottle is a blend of China cassia cinnamon, star anise, anise seed, ginger and cloves. In addition to chicken and five spice powder, the recipe calls for garlic, onion, celery, ginger, lemon zest and chicken broth. I served this over a rice blend from the pantry with a simple green salad. https://simple-nourished-living.com/skinny-slow-cooker-five-spice-chicken/

Slow Cooker Asian Braised Beef This Recipe is from Slow Cooker: The Best Cookbook Ever with More Than 400 Easy-to-Make Recipes, by Diane Phillips, who once lived in Japan. She describes it as a slow cooked variation on Sukiyaki. There's no browning required, so it's really easy. But you do need to marinate the meat overnight. Served with sticky rice to soak up the delicious sauce, this was an easy, healthy and delicious meal in a bowl. https://simple-nourished-living.com/weight-watchers-slow-cooker-asian-braised-beef/

Pedro Egurrola, 21, is one of the most talented young Mexican-American team ropers in Arizona. He grew up ranching —as did his father, and all his relatives as far back as they can remember— and started competing in rodeos when he was 10. Today, he lives in Casa Grande, Arizona, where he competes on a college rodeo team and works on horses. “I’ll probably be doing rodeo forever,” he said. Pictured here is Pockets shortly after his first ever time competing in the Tucson Rodeo. Pedro has 10 horses, and Pockets, he says, is the favorite. CLICK HERE TO READ Aspen Institute Latinos and Society Program - AILAS REPORT➡ https://ihccbusiness.net/research/ "In this white paper, which IHCC is part of, provokes reflection, mobilizes attention, and promotes targeted and context-sensitive engagement. This is how IHCC works every day to get things done. We are here to help small businesses to open and scale up," says Jaime di Paulo, President & CEO from the Illinois Hispanic Chamber of Commerce. EXCERPT: Latino entrepreneurs and small business owners were among the hardest hit by the pandemic, exacerbating existing inequalities. A lack of access to digital tools and critical capital caused a third of Latino-owned businesses to temporarily close or permanently shut down. Insufficient access to a digital safety net, including e-commerce channels, has continued to hamper the resilience and competitiveness of Latino businesses for the past two years. #digital #entrepreneurs #safety #smallbusiness

March 19 - 20, 2022 - Basic Principles of Somatic Experiencing® for BIPOC: Registration Link: https://cvent.me/28z0bn:=:https://web.cvent.com/event/8485e47b-e8a9-4860-9aa6-93e5c00a16f3 Honoring our commitment to serving the needs of those who have been under-represented in the SE community, Somatic Experiencing International is offering introductory workshops and training cohorts for BIPOC-only (Indigenous, Black, and otherwise identified People of Color) participants. This 2-day training is an introduction to Somatic Experiencing and gives an overview of the clinical training. Participants will be able to learn about the SE framework and skills within the environment of a BIPOC-only group and explore how the skills are applicable to themselves and their communities. To further provide for a sense of safety during the workshop we ask that participants agree to the following: • I confirm that I identify as Black/African American, Indigenous or a Person of Color • This program introduces a framework for working with trauma, therefore it is possible that I may be triggered or become uncomfortable during the training. I confirm that my mental health is such that I will be able to recognize my own discomfort and reach out for support if necessary • I agree to allow other registered participants the right to speak for themselves. As such I will refrain from assuming that someone else needs me to defend or speak for them in this training and will instead attend to my own experience. When registering you will be prompted to choose one of the fees listed below. Please choose whichever option works best for you. Full - $175 Mid - $100 Supported - $50 #somaticexperiencing #therapists #somatic #traumaeducation #nervoussystem #training #psychology #psychiatry #mentalhealthprofessional #workshop #introduction
